"reference_id": 0,
"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "1020: God, all-knowing",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1020",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The omniscience of God is that attribute by which he knows all things past, present and future. What is hidden from human sight is still known by God. Scripture stresses the wisdom of God in all his actions, and often grounds this in his all-embracing knowledge.</p>\n<h2>God's unique self-knowledge within the Trinity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:27\">MAT 11:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:15\">JHN 10:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:10-1Cor2:11\">1CO 2:10–2:11</a></p>\n<h2>The nature of God's knowledge</h2>\n<h3>God's knowledge originates within himself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:13-Isa40:14\">ISA 40:13–40:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:22\">JOB 21:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:33-Rom11:34\">ROM 11:33–11:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:16\">1CO 2:16</a></p>\n<h3>God's knowledge is complete</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:30\">MAT 10:30</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:7\">LUK 12:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:4\">PSA 147:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:26\">ISA 40:26</a></p>\n<h3>God knows things that are hidden from human understanding</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:29\">DEU 29:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job37:15-Job37:16\">JOB 37:15–37:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:22\">DAN 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:36\">MAT 24:36</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:32\">MRK 13:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:7\">ACT 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:2-2Cor12:4\">2CO 12:2–12:4</a></p>\n<h2>God's comprehensive knowledge of people</h2>\n<h3>God's knowledge of people's actions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:21\">JOB 34:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:23\">JOB 24:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:4\">JOB 31:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:13-Ps33:15\">PSA 33:13–33:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:2-Ps139:3\">PSA 139:2–139:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:24\">JER 23:24</a></p>\n<h3>God's knowledge of people's needs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:8\">MAT 6:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:31-Matt6:32\">MAT 6:31–6:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:29-Luke12:30\">LUK 12:29–12:30</a></p>\n<h3>God's knowledge of people's hearts and minds</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:9\">1CH 28:9</a></strong> <em>Scripture views the heart not primarily as the seat of emotion but more particularly as the seat of the will.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:20-Ps44:21\">PSA 44:20–44:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:1-Ps139:2\">PSA 139:1–139:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:10\">JER 17:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:5\">EZK 11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:12-Heb4:13\">HEB 4:12–4:13</a></p>\n<h3>God's knowledge of individuals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:1-Gen20:7\">GEN 20:1–20:7</a> <em>God's knowledge of Abimelech's motives and behaviour towards Abraham's wife Sarah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:1-1Sam16:12\">1SA 16:1–16:12</a> <em>the LORD to Samuel regarding David's anointing as king</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:1-Acts5:10\">ACT 5:1–5:10</a> <em>God's knowledge of the deception of Ananias and Sapphira</em></p>\n<h3>God's knowledge of people's sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:17\">JER 16:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job10:14\">JOB 10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:5\">PSA 69:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:22\">JER 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:2\">HOS 7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:12\">AMO 5:12</a></p>\n<h2>God's foreknowledge</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:10\">ISA 46:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:9\">ISA 42:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:7\">ISA 44:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:28\">DAN 2:28</a></p>\n<h3>God's foreknowledge of Jesus Christ's passion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:23\">ACT 2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:18\">ACT 3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:27-Acts4:28\">ACT 4:27–4:28</a></p>\n<h3>God's foreknowledge of those who would become disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:29\">ROM 8:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:5\">JER 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:2\">ROM 11:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>God's foreknowledge of people's free actions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:4\">PSA 139:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:19\">EXO 3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:21\">DEU 31:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam23:10-1Sam23:13\">1SA 23:10–23:13</a></p>\n<h2>Implications of God's knowledge</h2>\n<h3>God's knowledge ensures that all will be judged fairly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:13\">HEB 4:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:3\">1SA 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:22-Job34:23\">JOB 34:22–34:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:14\">ECC 12:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:16\">ROM 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:5\">1CO 4:5</a></p>\n<h3>God's knowledge ensures that he knows those who are his</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:19\">2TI 2:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:5\">NUM 16:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:12\">EXO 33:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job23:10\">JOB 23:10</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:14\">JHN 10:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:3\">1CO 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:9\">GAL 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:19-1John3:20\">1JN 3:19–3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:8\">REV 3:8</a></p>",
